-adding the `as` prop. I'm still rendering a totally accessible `<a>` link to the DOM, my wrapper component just adds some extra classes to style it. The same applies to the `style`, `target=\"_blank\"`, etc. props.\r\n\r\nIn my case, I cannot directly modify the `Link` component I'm passing to the `as` prop as it's provided by an external library. Yes, I can create _yet another_ Link wrapper that uses `useHref` and `useNavigate`, but imo 1. it's not scalable to large codebases with multiple link styles and 2. relies on react-router users making the Link component accessible when react-router already does a great job at this.","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/remix-run/react-router/issues/comments/687839805/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"hugmanrique","id":6255580,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYyNTU1ODA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6255580?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/hugmanrique","html_url":"https://github.com/hugmanrique","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hugmanrique/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hugmanrique/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hugmanrique/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hugmanrique/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hugmanrique/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hugmanrique/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hugmanrique/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hugmanrique/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hugmanrique/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"id":3965113533,"node_id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDM5NjUxMTM1MzM=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/re